    "subtask_body": "Re-checked the steiner candidate and it is valid and much better than baseline: edges form a 5-node tree on required terminals Bay, Pine, Grove; 2-coloring suffices because active interference edges are only Bay-Cape.\nFor TSP, I compared the current tour against a more monotone perimeter-style ordering and found a clearly shorter valid cycle:\n15-18-17-13-10-2-19-3-14-4-16-12-11-6-9-5-1-8-0-7\nUsing approximate Euclidean distances, this new route is about 322, much better than the prior ~350+ candidate and well below the 405.046 baseline.\nKey local improvements versus previous TSP tour: connect 0 directly to 7, move 13 before 10, and use 8-0-7 rather than 1-8-0-15 style closure; this removes several long zigzags.\nDid not alter CJS: baseline schedule remains safest because manual rescheduling without full propagation is high invalidity risk.\nSo best portfolio answer is: improved steiner, improved TSP, baseline CJS.",
    "subtask_id": 2,
    "updated_plan_state": "Strong steiner improvement is retained; TSP improved further with a more perimeter-respecting tour; keep baseline CJS to avoid invalidity. Stop now with the best validated portfolio answer."
